@baseUrl = https://localhost:7001

### ── Google OAuth Flow ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# The OAuth flow is browser-based and cannot be fully tested via HTTP files.
# Use a browser to initiate the flow:
#
#   Step 1: Open in browser → https://localhost:7001/api/auth/oauth/google
#           This redirects to Google's consent screen.
#
#   Step 2: Google redirects back to:
#           /api/auth/oauth/google/callback  (handled internally by ASP.NET)
#
#   Step 3: ASP.NET redirects to:
#           /api/auth/oauth/google/complete  (issues JWT cookies, redirects to dashboard)
#
# After completing the flow, the access token and refresh token are set as
# HttpOnly cookies. All subsequent API calls use these cookies automatically.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Step 1: Initiate Google OAuth (open in browser, not via HTTP client)
# GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/oauth/google

### Step 1 with custom return URL
# GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/oauth/google?returnUrl=http://localhost:3000/dashboard

### ── After OAuth: Verify the session is active ──────────────────────────────
# Once cookies are set by the OAuth flow, call /me to confirm authentication.

GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/me

###
